{"id": "ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM", "rating": 4.6, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_MODERATE", "userRatingCount": 4059, "displayName": {"text": "Hog Island Oyster Co.", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "Contemporary waterside seafood eatery serving local oysters and clams, plus craft cocktails.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKc1EwVkNaMmd5Y2xkVGFYSmFjM0IwUTBWQ00wRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Fantastic food, atmosphere and view. The waitress was horribly inattentive, but the other waitstaff were very helpful.\n\nThe (chilled) Dungeness crab was fresh, full and sweet. Delicious! Great presentation too.\n\nChose a dozen mixed raw oysters. The Sweetwater and Kumamoto were my favs. Well balanced and not too briny.\n\nOrdered some grilled oysters too. Really like the bourbon chipotle. Nice mild smokiness and spice.\n\nMichelin star in 2005. Food exemplified that star on my visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Fantastic food, atmosphere and view. The waitress was horribly inattentive, but the other waitstaff were very helpful.\n\nThe (chilled) Dungeness crab was fresh, full and sweet. Delicious! Great presentation too.\n\nChose a dozen mixed raw oysters. The Sweetwater and Kumamoto were my favs. Well balanced and not too briny.\n\nOrdered some grilled oysters too. Really like the bourbon chipotle. Nice mild smokiness and spice.\n\nMichelin star in 2005. Food exemplified that star on my visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "J C", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107389910800384993438/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKw0XckO-tNXm8heMhIgQrs99OEGIx257o7XMz0fXwXl9weGA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-27T04:55:24.167185941Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKc1EwVkNaMmd5Y2xkVGFYSmFjM0IwUTBWQ00wRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKc1EwVkNaMmd5Y2xkVGFYSmFjM0IwUTBWQ00wRRAB!2m1!1s0x808580668e8f3159:0x830980e627627a81"}, {"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200eE5uQlRSMDlMT0ZCemVGUk1lR3BDY2pBMldHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "WOW. The steamed seafood bowl here is on another level — so fresh and flavorful, I couldn’t get enough. Add in that stunning ocean view and the lively atmosphere, and it makes for a pretty unbeatable combo. I’d genuinely eat here every day if I could afford it! 😄 If you’re in SF and love seafood, this is a must-visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "WOW. The steamed seafood bowl here is on another level — so fresh and flavorful, I couldn’t get enough. Add in that stunning ocean view and the lively atmosphere, and it makes for a pretty unbeatable combo. I’d genuinely eat here every day if I could afford it! 😄 If you’re in SF and love seafood, this is a must-visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "L", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103382387179538538556/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVO-19WDe7pFAyJNEBk9QCyA7jTzaSutpBMaOy88dowaDRIdqh=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-24T18:17:03.825387782Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200eE5uQlRSMDlMT0ZCemVGUk1lR3BDY2pBMldHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200eE5uQlRSMDlMT0ZCemVGUk1lR3BDY2pBMldHYxAB!2m1!1s0x808580668e8f3159:0x830980e627627a81"}, {"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aTVpqVmlTRmhOWldSVlJuSldabko1VmpocVFtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Very busy at lunchtime on a Saturday - wait time outside was about 20 minutes or so and it was well worth it.  Clam chowder was excellent - very hearty, plenty of clams, and used my bread to insure I was able to get the last drops of broth.  Prices were $$$. Very friendly staff - service was fast.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Very busy at lunchtime on a Saturday - wait time outside was about 20 minutes or so and it was well worth it.  Clam chowder was excellent - very hearty, plenty of clams, and used my bread to insure I was able to get the last drops of broth.  Prices were $$$. Very friendly staff - service was fast.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Michael Howe", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101344812494822335129/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuBg9-IjPgcLM4cXOtgLqucDqsBlWu0DSBf5ox9AoKdJmhQQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-23T23:38:39.772247888Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aTVpqVmlTRmhOWldSVlJuSldabko1VmpocVFtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aTVpqVmlTRmhOWldSVlJuSldabko1VmpocVFtYxAB!2m1!1s0x808580668e8f3159:0x830980e627627a81"}, {"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKWWRGVkpiMVZGVEU5dGRXVmxkRTF1VFVWVVdHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Great food for a decent price, right in the Ferry Building! I’d always assumed this place would be a tourist trap, but I’m glad I gave it a shot. The oysters were amazing, and I got the shrimp po' boy sandwich, which was solid as well.\n\nI do wish there had been a bit more attention to service, e.g. our bread never arrived until we flagged someone down. That said, the food definitely made up for it. Overall, a solid spot, and I’d come back to try their clam chowder next time.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Great food for a decent price, right in the Ferry Building! I’d always assumed this place would be a tourist trap, but I’m glad I gave it a shot. The oysters were amazing, and I got the shrimp po' boy sandwich, which was solid as well.\n\nI do wish there had been a bit more attention to service, e.g. our bread never arrived until we flagged someone down. That said, the food definitely made up for it. Overall, a solid spot, and I’d come back to try their clam chowder next time.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jaewon Lee", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112674535225052303250/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV87LYcNDeLk74dnW6m9fkGmGzRGYuGI0LrUJpXtQnS7x14nUmb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-10T01:15:57.665134714Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKWWRGVkpiMVZGVEU5dGRXVmxkRTF1VFVWVVdHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKWWRGVkpiMVZGVEU5dGRXVmxkRTF1VFVWVVdHYxAB!2m1!1s0x808580668e8f3159:0x830980e627627a81"}, {"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xSaWNsVjRiSFZJU25GRWNrcFFaMEpDWTFOSlpIYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "If you enjoy seafood and fresh oysters, steamed clams, this is perfect! Located on boardwalk at Ferry Building, recommend for lunch or late afternoon to enjoy the view as well as people watching on the boardwalk. Servers are quick, food delicious and they don’t rush you although it can be busy given location. Enjoyed sitting outside but know that you may have people lining up right along your table. Will be going back for the chowder!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "If you enjoy seafood and fresh oysters, steamed clams, this is perfect! Located on boardwalk at Ferry Building, recommend for lunch or late afternoon to enjoy the view as well as people watching on the boardwalk. Servers are quick, food delicious and they don’t rush you although it can be busy given location. Enjoyed sitting outside but know that you may have people lining up right along your table. Will be going back for the chowder!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "CW", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108670372832633651628/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4W3N3MP6pFJToEC_upOMbHHirbzql-m36-j1ayg7Ujv48nag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-12T22:29:09.300381197Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xSaWNsVjRiSFZJU25GRWNrcFFaMEpDWTFOSlpIYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xSaWNsVjRiSFZJU25GRWNrcFFaMEpDWTFOSlpIYxAB!2m1!1s0x808580668e8f3159:0x830980e627627a81"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJWTGPjmaAhYARgXpiJ-aACYM/photos/AWCwydjeO0PnGFPwwGdKX1IoLE31PTEO-FdGIC4Bl3G2rZZZbtFhsQPXq0TX9Y56gFkDKsdt6EiGi9N6211EpB_m8oWIKY8Mk0AtuU71ajEsu0cn9DfJtYoYhzFgNv6DYfoYEGwdyMRo3fHtutr0ESWTemyp1m852mXPJklLlmrvVHkxgwwJpk8slcplkaJFSZ_86DLl8DyWEZT6hLGQnJ8wpYliR2lHFYwZcADFuE0fZfIof8H9XIR2gG9mBOPTul04XX_Kadxk75cx4FDkXNKhKhMTqFkthZgbd-eboG1msm9vqwYac3f0C19N6aP-trg3wETsXT-kiwgczxW671CtlnfdEuht3rjF-YaAw2SM9DrlVUNNkT9h-GPtnMjsFCyV6U_io7mdehA1wNmP7SEfE_9Iz10lxD4BhSztENBpJidUjVFc", "widthPx": 4800, "heightPx": 3120, "authorAttributions": [{"displayName": "Hog Island Oyster Co.", "uri": "https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/111592707657525468627", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6rRI9Nw_7_0LqJM9I39LlMYLpk0MhaB4jZKXUFnpLT28rrcI=s100-p-k-no-mo"}], "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/repor